class krrood.ormatic.ormatic.AlternativelyMaps#

Bases: krrood.class_diagrams.class_diagram.ClassRelation

Edge type that says that the source alternativly maps the target, e. g. AlternativeMaps(source=PointMapping, target=Point) means that PointMapping is the mapping for Point.

class krrood.ormatic.ormatic.ORMatic#

ORMatic is a tool for generating SQLAlchemy ORM models from a set of dataclasses.

class_dependency_graph: krrood.class_diagrams.class_diagram.ClassDiagram#

The class diagram to add the orm for.

alternative_mappings: typing_extensions.List[typing_extensions.Type[krrood.ormatic.dao.AlternativeMapping]] = []#

List of alternative mappings that should be used to map classes.

type_mappings: TypeMappingsType#

A dict that maps classes to custom types that should be used to save the classes. They keys of the type mappings must be disjoint with the classes given..

inheritance_strategy: krrood.ormatic.utils.InheritanceStrategy#

The inheritance strategy to use.

foreign_key_postfix = '_id'#

The postfix that will be added to foreign key columns (not the relationships).

imported_modules: sortedcontainers.SortedSet[str]#

A set of modules that need to be imported.

type_annotation_map: typing_extensions.Dict[str, str]#

The string version of type mappings that is used in jinja.

inheritance_graph: rustworkx.PyDiGraph[int] = None#

A graph that represents the inheritance structure of the classes. Extracted from the class dependency graph.

wrapped_tables: typing_extensions.Dict[krrood.class_diagrams.class_diagram.WrappedClass, krrood.ormatic.wrapped_table.WrappedTable]#

The wrapped tables instances for the SQLAlchemy conversion.

List of association tables for many-to-many relationships.
